{"data":[{"page":{"entry":{"name":"09_gaussianBlurFilter","filename":"09_gaussianBlurFilter","absolute":"/Users/gilbertsinnott/Code/openFrameworks/examples/shader/09_gaussianBlurFilter","path":"/examples/shader/09_gaussianBlurFilter/","dir":"../examples/shader","route":"/examples/shader/09_gaussianBlurFilter/","ext":"","type":"folder","id":1551,"children":[1552,1553,1554],"parent":1505,"breadcrumbs":[1505,436],"siblings":[],"translations":{}},"intro":{"name":"README","filename":"README.md","absolute":"/Users/gilbertsinnott/Code/openFrameworks/examples/shader/09_gaussianBlurFilter/README.md","path":"/examples/shader/09_gaussianBlurFilter/README","route":"/examples/shader/09_gaussianBlurFilter/README.md","dir":"../examples/shader/09_gaussianBlurFilter","ext":"md","type":"page","id":1553,"parent":1551,"breadcrumbs":[1551,1505,436],"translations":{},"siblings":[]},"document":"<h1>About Gaussian Blue Filter Example</h1>\n<p><img src=\"gaussianBlurFilterExample.png\" alt=\"Screenshot of Example, stored as exampleName/screenshot.png (or .gif or .jpg)\"></p>\n<h3>Learning Objectives</h3>\n<p>This openFrameworks example demonstrates how to apply a gaussian blur filter to an image in multiple passes.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Use of <code>shaderBlurX</code> and <code>shaderBlurY</code>, two <a href=\"http://openframeworks.cc/documentation/gl/ofShader/\">ofShader</a> objects</li>\n<li>Use of <code>fboBlurOnePass</code> and <code>fboBlurTwoPass</code>, two [ofFbo] (http://openframeworks.cc/documentation/gl/ofFbo/) objects use as offscreen rendering containers</li>\n<li>Blur amount deteremined by position of the mouse: <code><span class=\"token keyword\">float</span> blur <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">ofMap</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>mouseX<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token function\">ofGetWidth</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token boolean\">true</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></li>\n<li>Use of <code>shaderBlurX<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">setUniform1f</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">&amp;</span>quot<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>blurAmnt<span class=\"token operator\">&amp;</span>quot<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> blur<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code> to the set the horizontal blur amount</li>\n<li>Use of <code>shaderBlurY<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">setUniform1f</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">&amp;</span>quot<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>blurAmnt<span class=\"token operator\">&amp;</span>quot<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> blur<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code> to the set the vertical blur amount</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Expected Behavior</h3>\n<p>When launching this application, you will see a brightly patterned image.</p>\n<p>Instructions for use:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Move the mouse on the horizon to see the increase the blur amount</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Other classes used in this file</h3>\n<p>No other classes were used for this example.</p>\n","type":"folder"}}],"fetch":[]}